	)
	(text "Notes \n\n- Vin is limited to max gate VGS on the input \n  reverse protection MOSFET and limited by Ven.\n- Vout can be set changing Vfb using R Trimmer.\n\nFormulas\n\n- Ven = {R3/(R1+R2) + R3]}Vin *Voltage Divider Formula\n  => (100K / 300K) Vin \n\n- Lmin = Vout(Vinmax - Vout) / Vinmaax x Kind x Iout x Fsw  	\n  *Equation 8 in the datasheet\n  Assuming Iout = 3A, Fsw = 350Khz, Kind = 0.3 , Vinmax = 18V\n  => @Vout = 3.3V => 3.3(18 - 3.3) / 18 x 0.3 x 3 x 350K => 8uH\n  => @Vout = 5V => 11.46uH\n  => @Vout = 12V => 12.69uH\n  From the above calculated minimum inductance values 14uH should be enough.\n\n- Vout = Vref[{R4/(R5 + R6)}+1]		    *Equation 7 in the datasheet\n  => 0.597[{100K/(5K + R Trimmer)}+1]   *Vref = 0.597V from the datasheet\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 83.82 172.466 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(italic yes)
				(color 132 0 0 1)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "bb8c1ac2-5ccb-4e2e-b2b8-037661372768")
	)
